headlines.description: — The Indiana Pacers produced the perfect celebration Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam has triple-double, Pacers end 76ers' winning streak at 6 with 134-122 victory

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 27 points, Anthony Edwards added 24 and the Western Conference-leading Minnesota Timberwolves held on for a 96-94 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 27 points, Edwards gets 24, Timberwolves hang on for 96-94 win over Nets

headlines.description: — Boston coach Joe Mazzulla is a movie buff who made big news last season when revealing that he watches “The Town” several times a week. And he recently watched the 1993 crime drama “A Bronx Tale,” another movie that earned his two-thumbs-up rating.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 26 points, Celtics embarrass Heat in East finals rematch, 143-110

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored 26 points, Jalen Brunson added 21 and the New York Knicks handed the defending NBA champion Denver Nuggets their worst loss of the season, 122-84 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby, Brunson lead surging Knicks to 122-84 rout of Nuggets

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — When Harrison Barnes starts feeling it, the Sacramento Kings look for him in any spot he likes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis dunks with 22 seconds left, Curry loses ball as Kings hold on to beat Warriors 134-133

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 25 points and 12 assists a few hours after being named to his record 20th NBA All-Star team and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Chicago Bulls 141-132 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron, Russell lead the Lakers' impressive shooting in a 141-132 victory over Chicago
